<div id="review_3927465771" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3927465771" />
    <a title="Micah Cummins" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/66666194-micah-cummins"><img alt="Micah Cummins" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1621610811p2/66666194.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3927465771?book_show_action=true">Apr 09, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Micah Cummins" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Micah Cummins" href="/user/show/66666194-micah-cummins">Micah Cummins</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3927465771" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer15459827845200593405"><i>The Joy Luck Club</i> by Amy Tan is the story four Chinese immigrant families living in San Fransisco who start a club playing Mahjong and feasting on their favorite meals. Throughout these meetings, four mothers, four daughters, and four families stories are interwoven. The mothers and daughters are shown in contrast through most of the plot. The mothers want their daughters to be more Chinese, while the daughters wish their mothers would be more interested in their American lives, and their new wa</span>
  <span id="freeText15459827845200593405" style="display:none"><i>The Joy Luck Club</i> by Amy Tan is the story four Chinese immigrant families living in San Fransisco who start a club playing Mahjong and feasting on their favorite meals. Throughout these meetings, four mothers, four daughters, and four families stories are interwoven. The mothers and daughters are shown in contrast through most of the plot. The mothers want their daughters to be more Chinese, while the daughters wish their mothers would be more interested in their American lives, and their new ways of living, which are often in conflict with the old ways their mothers know. All in all, I really enjoyed <i> The Joy Luck Club</i> I was moved by many of the stories, and felt attached to many characters by the end. Four stars. </span>
  <a data-text-id="15459827845200593405" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


